<module>
    <h>Màiri</h>
    <p><g>Màiri</g>
        <en>Mary</en> is a feminine <a href="?xx=nouns/anthroponymic_proper_nouns">anthroponymic
            proper noun</a>.</p>


    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>The principal parts of <g>Màiri</g> are – <ul>
                <li><m>Màiri</m> – nominative/dative/genitive (singular)</li>
                <li><m>A Mhàiri!</m> – vocative</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p>Examples with <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>Màiri</m> beag.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary is small.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>Màiri</m> ag obair.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary is working.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p>In a conjoined subject with <a href="?gd=agus"><g>agus</g></a>
                <en>and</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>Màiri</m> agus Calum ag obair anns an achadh an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and Malcolm are working in the field today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6–7</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

</module>
